Source: libgebr
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Ricardo Biloti <biloti@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 5)
Standards-Version: 3.7.2

Package: libgebr-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: GêBR library collecion
 GêBR is an environment to seismic processing based on open-source
 technologies, designed to easily assembly and run processing flows.
 .
 What GêBR does:
 .
     * Handle projects and lines
     * Assembly and run processing flows
     * Act as an interface to many freely-available seismic-processing
       packages (Seismic Unix, Madagascar, etc)
 .
 libgebr is the collection of libraries of GêBR:
     * libgebr_geoxml is the XML engine of GêBR
     * libgebr_misc network and process classes.
 .
 This package contains the header files, static libraries and symbolic
 links that developers using libgebr will need.
 .


